# 🎯 What is an Event Listener?

### ✅ English:

An **Event Listener** is a function that “listens” for an event (like click, hover, typing) and executes code when that event occurs.

### ✅ हिंदी:

Event Listener एक function होता है जो किसी event (जैसे click, typing) को सुनता है और उसके होने पर code चलाता है।

---

# 🔹 Syntax of addEventListener ⭐

```javascript
element.addEventListener(event, callback, options);
```

### Example:

```javascript
let btn = document.querySelector("button");

btn.addEventListener("click", function() {
    console.log("Button clicked!");
});
```

---

# 🔹 Breakdown

| Part     | Meaning            |
| -------- | ------------------ |
| event    | "click", "input"   |
| callback | function to run    |
| options  | bubbling/capturing |

---

# 🔥 Why use addEventListener?

| Feature                  | Benefit |
| ------------------------ | ------- |
| Multiple handlers        | Yes     |
| Cleaner code             | Yes     |
| Control (capture/bubble) | Yes     |

---

# 🔥 Basic Examples

---

## 1. Click Event

```javascript
btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    alert("Clicked!");
});
```

---

## 2. Input Event

```javascript
let input = document.querySelector("input");

input.addEventListener("input", (e) => {
    console.log(e.target.value);
});
```

👉 हिंदी: typing करते ही value मिलती है

---

## 3. Mouse Events

```javascript
box.addEventListener("mouseover", () => {
    box.style.backgroundColor = "red";
});
```

---

# 🔥 Event Object (Very Important)

```javascript
btn.addEventListener("click", function(event) {
    console.log(event);
});
```

### Useful Properties:

| Property      | Meaning         |
| ------------- | --------------- |
| event.target  | clicked element |
| event.type    | event name      |
| event.clientX | mouse X         |
| event.key     | key pressed     |

---

## Example:

```javascript
document.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    console.log("Clicked on:", e.target);
});
```

---

# 🔥 Multiple Event Listeners

```javascript
btn.addEventListener("click", () => console.log("First"));
btn.addEventListener("click", () => console.log("Second"));
```

👉 Output:

```
First
Second
```

---

# 🔥 Removing Event Listener

```javascript
function handleClick() {
    console.log("Clicked");
}

btn.addEventListener("click", handleClick);

// remove
btn.removeEventListener("click", handleClick);
```

👉 Important: same function reference चाहिए

---

# 🔥 Event Bubbling vs Capturing

---

## Bubbling (default)

```javascript
child → parent → document
```

```javascript
div.addEventListener("click", () => console.log("DIV"));
button.addEventListener("click", () => console.log("BUTTON"));
```

👉 Output:

```
BUTTON
DIV
```

---

## Capturing

```javascript
div.addEventListener("click", handler, true);
```

👉 हिंदी: ऊपर से नीचे

---

# 🔥 stopPropagation()

```javascript
btn.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    e.stopPropagation();
});
```

👉 Stops event flow

---

# 🔥 Event Delegation (Important 🔥)

---

## Problem:

Dynamic elements don't have listeners

## Solution:

Use parent

```javascript
document.querySelector("ul").addEventListener("click", function(e) {
    if(e.target.tagName === "LI") {
        console.log("Clicked:", e.target.innerText);
    }
});
```

---

### Hindi:

Parent से child events handle करना

---

# 🔥 Options in addEventListener

```javascript
element.addEventListener("click", handler, {
    once: true,
    capture: true
});
```

---

| Option  | Meaning              |
| ------- | -------------------- |
| once    | runs only once       |
| capture | use capturing        |
| passive | improves performance |

---

# 🔥 Keyboard Events

```javascript
document.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
    console.log(e.key);
});
```

---

# 🔥 Real Project Example 🔥

---

## Add Task Button

```html
<input id="task">
<button id="add">Add</button>
<ul id="list"></ul>
```

```javascript
let btn = document.getElementById("add");

btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    let value = document.getElementById("task").value;

    let li = document.createElement("li");
    li.innerText = value;

    document.getElementById("list").appendChild(li);
});
```

---

# 🔥 Common Interview Questions

---

## 1. Difference: onclick vs addEventListener

| onclick     | addEventListener |
| ----------- | ---------------- |
| One handler | Multiple         |
| Old         | Modern           |

---

## 2. Why removeEventListener not working?

👉 Because function reference different होता है

---

## 3. What is event.target vs this?

* `event.target` → actual clicked
* `this` → attached element

---

# 🧠 Summary

---

* Event Listener = event + function
* Use `addEventListener` (best practice)
* Supports bubbling & capturing
* Can handle multiple events
* Used everywhere in web apps

---

# 💡 Pro Tips

* Always use `addEventListener`
* Use event delegation for performance
* Use `once` for one-time actions
